<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-1101 </DOCNO><TEXT>A conveying liquid for transporting coal from deep seams to the surface,consisting of a concentrated aqueous salt solution having a density ofnot less than 1.39 g/cm{sup 3}, wherein substances which have a largenumber of hydroxyl groups in the molecule are added to the concentratedsalt solution, the said substances immobilizing the remaining water moleculesnot associated with the salts, so that penetration of the remaining waterinto slate or clay slate strata adjacent to the coal seams is prevented.</TEXT></DOC>